          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Cincinnati Ohio</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>23 February 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Rev Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I received in due course your favor of<lb/> the
                                        14th Inst.: I perceived the notice taken of the
                                        Retrospects<lb/> in the <date>February</date> number of the
                                        Occident, and now hand<lb/> you a circular containing
                                        notices of the work by the Press here<lb/> which please
                                        insert at large in your April number of the<lb/> Occident,
                                        and send your amount for the same to
                                                  <persName>Messieurs<lb/> Robinson</persName> and
                                                  <persName>Jones</persName> of this City.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr Guthrie</persName>, the partner of
                                                  <persName>Mr. Elias Mayer</persName><lb/> has
                                        kindly taken charge of this and of 50 Copies of the<lb/>
                                        Retrospect: I feel obliged by your pronure[?] to bring
                                        them<lb/> under the notice of your friends and shall be glad
                                        to see<lb/> the work received in the Occident</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I need not tell you who must have had<lb/>
                                        sufficient experience of the fact, how much exertion must
                                        be<lb/> used to preserve from loss there who engage in
                                        similar efforts<lb/> as these on behalf of our people: As
                                        yet I am minus 2/3 d.<lb/> the cost of printing the
                                        Retrospect but through the influence<lb/> of Gentlemen like
                                        yourself I trust I shall not be a sufferer<lb/> to any
                                        extent in the end: I have not sought to make money<lb/>
                                        through this channel but I confess my inability to sustain<lb/>
                                        <sic>conviniently</sic> any loss from it. I wrote
                                                  <persName>Rabbi Lilienthall</persName><lb/> and
                                        the <persName>Revd Aurel Leo</persName> but as yet have not
                                        been favored<lb/> with any reply—I am reverend Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Your obt. Servant</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <persName role="author">A A Lindo</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee>–</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>Favored by</p>
                              <p>
                                        <persName>Mr. A. A. Guthrie</persName>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
